The first shower we had, flooded the shower room and made the floor slippery and dangerous.	The wardrobe had a safe inside and big mirrors on the doors.	Venice is worth visiting for say three days - albeit you need to have a safe on your back to pay for the extortionate prices.	The room had a spacious bathroom with a bathtub and was nice decorated with a big mirror above the sink and a big mirror on the bathroom door.	The rooms were clean, well maintained, and a good size for a hotel in Venice.	The room was small, which to my understanding is common is Europe, but it was cozy, clean and had a good sized bathroom.